-- Copper Advances to a Record in New York For Second Day Amid Rising Demand
-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 2010-12-28T00:33:37Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-28/copper-advances-to-a-record-in-new-york-for-second-day-amid-rising-demand.html
Copper futures in New York climbed
to a record $4.3075 a pound, surpassing the previous peak of
$4.2985 a pound reached yesterday. The most-active March-
delivery contract on the Comex in New York traded at $4.3025 a
pound by 8:32 a.m. Singapore time.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Glenys Sim at 
